{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbcf7bb7b-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s775"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"775"},"text":"§ 775.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Refunds","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbcf7bb7c-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s775/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A Comptroller General separated from office before becoming entitled to receive an annuity under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s772"},"text":"section 772 of this title","children":[],"tail":" is entitled to a lump-sum refund of the amount deducted from pay or deposited as a contribution under section 772, plus 3 percent interest on the amount compounded every December 31."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbcf7bb7d-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s775/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A Comptroller General making an election under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s773"},"text":"section 773 of this title","children":[],"tail":" who is separated from office before becoming entitled to an annuity under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s772"},"text":"section 772 of this title","children":[],"tail":" is entitled to a lump-sum refund of the amount deducted under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s773"},"text":"section 773 of this title","children":[],"tail":", plus 4 percent interest before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1948-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 1948","children":[],"tail":", and 3 percent interest after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1947-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1947","children":[],"tail":", compounded every December 31 until the separation date."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbcf7bb7e-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s775/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" A lump-sum refund of the amounts deducted under sections 772 and 773 of this title, plus interest of 4 percent before ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1948-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 1948","children":[],"tail":", and 3 percent after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1947-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1947","children":[],"tail":", compounded every December 31 until the date of death, shall be paid under subsection (d) of this section if—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbcf7bb7f-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s775/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a Comptroller General dies in office before completing 5 years of civilian service under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s774"},"text":"section 774 of this title","children":[],"tail":" or after completing 5 years of civilian service but without a survivor entitled to an annuity under section 774(b) and (c) of this title; or"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbcf7bb80-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s775/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" if a retired Comptroller General dies without a survivor entitled to an annuity under section 774(b) and (c) of this title.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbcf7bb81-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s775/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" If a Comptroller General or retired Comptroller General dies before a refund is made under this section, the refund shall be paid in the following order of precedence:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbcf7bb82-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s775/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to a beneficiary the Comptroller General or retired Comptroller General designated in writing if the designation was received by the Government Accountability Office before the death of the Comptroller General or retired Comptroller General.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbcf7bb83-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s775/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to a surviving spouse.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbcf7bb84-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s775/d/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to the children and to a descendant of a deceased child by representation.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbcf7bb85-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s775/d/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to the parents equally or, if only one surviving parent, to that survivor.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbcf7bb86-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s775/d/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to the executor or administrator of the estate of the Comptroller General or retired Comptroller General.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbcf7bb87-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s775/d/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to the next of kin that the General Counsel of the Government Accountability Office decides is entitled to the refund under the laws of the domicile of the Comptroller General or retired Comptroller General at the time of death.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbcf7bb88-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s775/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The General Counsel is not subject to section 771(1) and (2) of this title when making a decision about a surviving spouse or child under subsection (c) or (d) of this section.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbcf7bb89-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s775/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" If the annuities of all individuals entitled to survivor annuities under this subchapter end before the amount of annuities paid equals the amount deducted under sections 772 and 773 of this title, plus interest of 4 percent before ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1948-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 1948","children":[],"tail":", and 3 percent after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1947-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1947","children":[],"tail":", compounded every December 31 until the date of death, the remainder shall be paid under subsection (d) of this section."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbcf7bb8a-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/258"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–258","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-09-13"},"text":"Sept. 13, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/905"},"text":"96 Stat. 905","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/271/s8/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–271, § 8(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-07-07"},"text":"July 7, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/814"},"text":"118 Stat. 814","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbcf7bb8b-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idbcf7bb8c-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idbcf7bb8d-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:thead","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{"colspan":"3"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Revised Section","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (U.S. Code)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (Statutes at Large)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tbody","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"775(a)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"31:43(last par. 1st sentence).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1921-06-10/ch18"},"text":"June 10, 1921, ch. 18","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/42/20"},"text":"42 Stat. 20","children":[],"tail":", § 303(last par.); added "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Oct. 25, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/512/s4/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–512, § 4(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/1801"},"text":"92 Stat. 1801","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"775(b)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"31:43b(i).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1921-06-10/ch18"},"text":"June 10, 1921, ch. 18","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/42/20"},"text":"42 Stat. 20","children":[],"tail":", § 319(i), (j)(less last 13 words before colon), (k); added "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"July 13, 1959","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/87"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–87","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/73/198"},"text":"73 Stat. 198","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"775(c)–(e)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"31:43(last par. last sentence).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"31:43b(j)(less last 13 words before colon).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"775(f)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"31:43b(k).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsections (a) and (b), the word “total” is omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a), the word “pay” is substituted for “salary” for consistency in the revised title and with other titles of the United States Code. The words “by him” and “to his annuity” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b), the words “who has elected to bring himself within the purview of” are omitted as surplus. The word “annuity” is substituted for “retirement pay” for consistency in the revised title and with other titles of the Code.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (c), before clause (1), the words “A lump-sum refund of the amounts deducted under sections 772 and 773 of this title” are substituted for “total amount deducted from his salary and retirement pay” for clarity. The words “under subsection (d) of this section” are added because of the restatement. The words “to the person or persons surviving at the date title to payment arises” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (d), the words before clause (1) are included for clarity. In clauses (2)–(4) and (6), the words “of such Comptroller General or retired Comptroller General” are omitted as surplus. In clause (5), the words “duly appointed” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (e), the words “of a Comptroller General or retired Comptroller General” are omitted as surplus. The words “is not subject to” are substituted for “shall be made . . . without regard to the definitions of these terms in” to eliminate unnecessary words.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (f), the word “individuals” is substituted for “persons” for consistency. The word “aggregate” is omitted as surplus. The words “under sections 772 and 773 of this title” are substituted for “total . . . from the salary and retirement pay of a Comptroller General or retired Comptroller General” for clarity and consistency. The word “under” is substituted for “in the order of precedence prescribed in” to eliminate unnecessary words.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbcf7bb8e-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idbcf7bb8f-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2004—Subsec. (d)(1), (6). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/271"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–271","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Government Accountability Office” for “General Accounting Office”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
